steps.instruction:
Present this C++11 non-recursive pattern and ask the learner to manually expand it for Args={int,double,std::string} and predict stdout:

```cpp
template<typename Arg, typename... Args>
void doPrint(std::ostream& out, Arg&& arg, Args&&... args) {
    out << arg;
    using expander = int[];
    (void)expander{0, (void(out << ", " << args), 0)...};
}
```

Ask specifically: why is the first argument peeled off, and what does the `(void)` cast accomplish with respect to operator, overloading?
